Module-Build-&Module-Build-version;
Module-Build
Module::Build allows perl modules to be built without a make command being present. This module uses the standard . If your version of perl is 5.20.2 or earlier, a version of this module was installed as part of the core perl distribution and you do not need to install a newer version.
When creating the Makefile, this module will report inc_bundling_support....disabled requires: ! inc::latest is not installed but inc::latest is experimental and not needed.
